In [[organizational development]], '''chaos theory''' is a subset of more general [[chaos theory]] that incorporates principles of [[quantum mechanics]] and presents them in a [[complex system]]s environment. To the observer the systems seem to be in chaos. Organizational Development of a business system is the management of that apparent chaos. The term “Managing Organized Chaos” is used in the book by the same name Managing Organized Chaos – Business Planning 1.0, to describe the daily management of an entity (business) engaged in continual activity.
